---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const skillText = `# Identity Engineer Contributor Skill

## Purpose
Guide contributors to improve Identity Engineering content with clarity, rigor, and boundary discipline.

## Contribution rules
1. Preserve distinction: core source theory vs IE interpretation vs IE additions.
2. Mark claims as conceptual, formal, or empirical where relevant.
3. Avoid overclaim language (no universal framing, no pseudo-certainty).
4. Keep analogies explicit as analogies unless formal mapping exists.
5. Maintain public transparency on open gaps and limitations.

## Review checklist
- Is the original source theory represented fairly?
- Is IE inspiration clearly separated from IE additions?
- Are scope and non-use boundaries visible?
- Is wording precise and non-guru-like?
- Are references and links present where needed?

## Output format
- Proposed change
- Why it improves rigor
- Scope/boundary impact
- Suggested follow-up edits`;
---

<Layout title="Identity Engineer Contributor Skill | Identity Engineering">
	<main class="min-h-screen px-6 pt-28 pb-20">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
			<div class="mb-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Skills</div>
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-6">Identity Engineer Contributor Skill</h1>
			<p class="text-white/55 mb-8">Canonical contributor skill text for agent ingestion.</p>
			<pre class="whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/30 p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/85">{skillText}</pre>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
